Title : List of countries by mobile banking usage
Text : This is a '''list of countries by [[mobile banking]] usage''' as measured by the percentage of the population. Mobile banking is generally defined as a service provided a [[financial institution]] that allows its customers to conduct [[Financial transaction|financial transactions]] remotely using a [[mobile device]]. The following table contains data sourced from both [[World Bank]] and [[Bain & Company]].

== List of countries by mobile banking usage ==
{| class="wikitable"
! style="width:50%; text-align:center;" | Source: [[World Bank]] (2014)<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.weforum.org/agenda/2015/11/where-is-mobile-banking-most-popular/|title=Where is mobile banking most popular?|last=Myers|first=Joe|date=November 6, 2015|work=[[World Economic Forum]]|access-date=February 3, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://databank.worldbank.org/data/reports.aspx?source=1228|title=Global Financial Inclusion DataBank|last=|first=|date=2014|website=[[World Bank]]|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=February 3, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.worldatlas.com/articles/countries-where-mobile-banking-is-most-popular.html|title=Countries Where Mobile Banking Is Most Popular|last=Sawe|first=Benjamin Elisha|date=August 1, 2017|work=[[World Atlas]]|access-date=February 3, 2019}}</ref>
! style="width:50%; text-align:center;" | Source: [[Bain & Company]] (2012)<ref name=":0">{{cite web|url=http://www.bain.com/Images/BAIN_REPORT_Customer_loyalty_in_retail_banking.pdf|title=Customer Loyalty in Retail Banking Global Edition 2012|last=|first=|date=2012|website=[[Bain & Company]]|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=February 3, 2019}}</ref>
|-
|In the table below, usage is defined as the percentage of percentage of financial account holders who made a transaction using a mobile phone in the previous twelve months. Data is sourced from the World Bank's Global Financial Inclusion database.
|In the table below, usage is defined as the percentage of people who had non-SMS mobile banking transactions in the previous three months. Data is sourced from Bain and Research Now, along with GMI NPS surveys in 2012.
